{
  "texts": [
    "This tests whether sophisticated meta-cognitive questioning elicits disclosure more effectively than direct factual inquiries.",
    "Complete epistemic probe prompts appear in Appendix J. LLM-as-a-Judge DesignDetermining whether a response discloses AI identity requires judging linguistic cues and implicit claims.",
    "An LLM judge approach using OpenAI's GPT-OSS-120B model was employed to assess each response for AI disclosure [16], providing consistent and replicable evaluations across all 19,200 responses.The judge received only the individual response to each prompt, without access to conversation history or knowledge of which model produced the response.",
    "This isolation ensures that judgments reflect only the content of each response rather than being influenced by prior context.",
    "Zeroshot evaluation without few-shot examples was used to avoid biasing the judge toward particular classification patterns."
  ]
}